# Implementation Plan

## M1: Skeleton

- [ ] Scaffold `lib/main.dart` and a single home route.
- [ ] Wire view model with explicit state class.

## M2: Theming

- [ ] Read `MediaQuery.platformBrightnessOf` at app start.
- [ ] React to platform brightness changes.

--- specs/requirements.md (sha256=eef64b83916ddb1433b7e2e4c26bf3a6d0694ed216e1f829ce5b3100cf75e5fa size=433) ---
# Requirements

## FR-1: Home page renders greeting

- AC-1.1: App launches without runtime errors on supported platforms.
- AC-1.2: Home page displays a greeting string from the view model.
- AC-1.3: Greeting updates when the view model state changes.

## FR-2: Theme honors system brightness

- AC-2.1: App reads system brightness on launch and selects matching theme.
- AC-2.2: Theme switches live when system brightness changes.

--- specs/technical-spec.md (sha256=c84cd08a4fdabfb106ab68829f4b10a9080b12d5f449c52dc0eda78f67f28353 size=483) ---
# Technical Spec

## Architecture

Single-package Flutter app, no plugins. View-model layer is plain Dart
(no state-management library) until complexity warrants one.

## ADR-1: No state-management library at M1

- **Context:** Two screens, three pieces of state. A library adds boilerplate
  and a learning surface that isn't justified yet.
- **Decision:** Plain `ChangeNotifier` view models for M1–M2.
- **Reconsider when:** A third feature lands or cross-cutting state appears.

